About Me

Hello,my name is Jingjing Han. I am an Associate Professor of Emerging Technologies at the School of Journalism at Fudan University.

My research focuses on dynamic changes of cognitive and emotional processing during human-human and human-machine/media communication，using the complex dynamic systems framework as the primary approach.

I currently serve the Vice Chair Elect of the Information Systems Division of ICA, and Associate Editor of Cognitive Science.

I obtained my Ph.D in media arts and sciences at the Media School of Indiana University Bloomington.
